review_blob: Definitely not impressed with this beer. Not much subtlety in the rather harsh burnt malty aromas and taste. Not well balanced, watery, not enough sweetness or fullness. Bitterness unpleasantly lingering.

Bought in Co-op Buckfastleigh, UK. Braille on label. Surprisingly wonderful beer, this. Aromaa of both honey, horsy hops and fresh hops. Very pleasant honey taste while malt and hops were not forgotten. Strong but well-balanced bitterness, lingering on nicely together with hop aromas after swallowing. Very Good Stuff.
